# Agent Gradle Cache

When an agent runs Gradle in this repo, use the user's warm Gradle cache instead of Cursor's isolated sandbox cache.

Always prefix Gradle and local build/check commands with:

```bash
GRADLE_USER_HOME="$HOME/.gradle"
```

Examples:

```bash
GRADLE_USER_HOME="$HOME/.gradle" ./gradlew help --no-daemon
GRADLE_USER_HOME="$HOME/.gradle" ./gradlew detekt apiCheck --parallel --build-cache
GRADLE_USER_HOME="$HOME/.gradle" ./local-checks.sh --pra --json
```

Keep using `required_permissions: ["all"]` for Gradle commands because Gradle daemon/build tooling needs unrestricted filesystem and socket access.

Reason: Cursor agents may default `GRADLE_USER_HOME` to an isolated cache under `/var/folders/.../cursor-sandbox-cache`, which can miss already-downloaded Android artifacts from `~/.gradle` and trigger network failures when resolving Google Maven dependencies.
